  dialogNodes:
  - startTime: 0
    showTime: 0
    description: 'The Vault has been sealed for three hundred years. The seal was never meant to be permanent — it was an emergency measure.'
    nextOption: What was it sealing?
  - startTime: 0
    showTime: 0
    description: 'A dragon. Old enough that the factions''s ancestors were not yet factions when it was bound.'
    nextOption: Is it still alive?
  - startTime: 0
    showTime: 0
    description: 'Very much so. It dreams. Those dreams leak upward through the stone — soldiers who sleep near the entrance report them.'
    nextOption: What do they dream?
  - startTime: 0
    showTime: 0
    description: 'Open spaces. Heat. A voice speaking in a language they don''t know but understand perfectly. None of them sleep near the entrance twice.'
    nextOption: Can the seal hold?
  - startTime: 0
    showTime: 0
    description: 'It has held three hundred years. Three of its nine panels are cracked. At current deterioration rate — she pauses to calculate — another thirty years. Perhaps less if the fighting continues.'
    nextOption: The fighting is damaging it?
  - startTime: 0
    showTime: 0
    description: 'Vibration. Explosions. The structural integrity of the chamber is not what it was. Both factions are accelerating the timeline without knowing it.'
    nextOption: 
  prerequisiteConditions: []
